<subSubSection pageId="38" pageNumber="167" type="conservation">
<paragraph blockId="38.[92,1299,727,1470]" pageId="38" pageNumber="167">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[94,450,1160,1193]" pageId="38" pageNumber="167">Status and Conservation.</emphasis>
Classified as Data Deficient on The IUCN Red List. Olrog’s Four-eyed Opossum is known only from very few specimens collected 30-40 years ago, and there is virtually no information on its status, population size, and habitat requirements. It may be threatened by loss of habitat in Bolivia because expansion of agriculture is causing habitat loss in lowland forests. Olrog’s Four-eyed Opossum probably occurs in Parque Nacional Carrasco and Parque Nacional Amboro, but there are no vouchered records ofits presence in protected areas in Bolivia.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
